<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-01T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="125" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Hungary/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Brentano</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-01T09:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                        1922—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 2—3:51
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>40. Your circular telegram dated April 21, noon. Hungarian Minister
                            Foreign Affairs states Hungary will be represented on <pb facs="0523" n="403" xml:id="pg_403"/> World War Foreign Debt Commission.
                                Széchényi<note n="25" xml:id="d125fn25">Count László Széchényi,
                                Hungarian Minister to the United States.</note> representative,
                                Pelényi<note n="26" xml:id="d125fn26">John Pelényi, Hungarian
                                Counselor of Legation at Washington.</note> deputy.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Brentano</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>